e book is not formally a commentary on Aspasius’ commentary; but between them the essays consider the interpretation of numerous problematic or significant passages. Full indices will enable readers quickly to locate discussion of particular parts of Aspasius’ work. This volume of essays will form a natural complement to the first ever translation of Aspasius’ commentary into any modern language, currently in preparation by Paul Mercken.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEthics, Ancient. 4aAristoteles: Ethica Nicomachea. 4aAspasius ‹Philosophus›. 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aKommentar. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh1 aAlberti, Antonina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlberti, Antonina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBarnes, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerti, Enrico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIerodiakonou, Katerina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSedley, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharples, Bob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharples, Robert W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSorabji, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTausch-Pebody, Gudrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWittwer, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 1990 - 1999z9783110636116oZDB-23-GCN0 cprintz978311016081940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311081019640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110810196423Coveruh